Pelvic arcade ( Fig. 17 ,
Plate XXVII
). The pelvic arcade is distinguished by the following characters: (1) the antero-posterior extension of the ilium; (2) the firm articulation of the ilium with the sacral ribs ( Fig. 16 , S 1-S 5); (3) the articulation of the ilium with the metapophyses of the three posterior sacrals ( Fig. 16 , S3-S5); (4) the anterior expansion of the iliac plates ( Fig. 16 C ); (5) the postero-intemal iliac horizontal plates ( Fig. 16 D ).
